begin_memory_text: We started discussing the weather. It's my go to question when it seems like we are going to struggle with making conversation
middle_memory_text: Working from home? I remember asking her about school and if her parents were too, where she was from we talked about vacations and trips
end_memory_text: She asked how my week has gone so far and what I had been up to, I started talking about food. I could discuss food for hours.
rest_of_day_open: I have a very busy week ahead. I see it going really well and very quickly because I have so many to-dos. We are headed to the beach soon so that helps me get through the weeks as well. Work is picking up, mandatory appointments means a lot more virtual discussions and works
critical_positive: I think my ability to talk to anyone helped get the discussion going and keep going. I think my list of go-to questions was helpful too. Both of us being pleasant meant we were able to take turns and understand to pretend we were interested in one another. Laughing helps a little too
critical_negative: Nothing in common. My partner seems like she is quiet and timid, so immediately I realized I had to try to carry the conversation. My iffy mood today made it harder for me to come up with decent topics and to be quick on my feet. If COVID weren't an issue, I don't know what we would've discussed since being at home dominated most of our conversation.

begin_memory_text: In the beginning, we just had a small talk about where we were from, what the weather was like and what we do for a living.
middle_memory_text: In the middle, we continued to talk about our jobs and how school was working out for the both of us amid covid. We talked about the details of how each other was handling things.
end_memory_text: In the end, we talked about the shows we watched and what we've been doing. She talked about how she has been cooking and trying new recipes.
rest_of_day_open: I see my week going great. I don't have a crazy amount of work and I am not super stressed about anything. I am really looking forward to the weekend since I have a lot planned with friends and my family is coming to visit me. It'll be a pretty good week.
critical_positive: We both talked about things we could relate to or share our experiences about. We had different perspectives on the same topic of education since she works in higher education and I am a student. We were both very receptive to each other and agreeable about general things like the pandemic.
critical_negative: We didn't have too much to talk about and were running out of things to say. We were more talking because we had to talk for a certain length than talking naturally. The conversation was a lot of office type talk about the weather, weekend, and small talk instead of a talk between acquaintances.
